<p>GDP growth: -0.2% GDP: $2,201bn (PPP: $1,994bn) Inflation: 1.8% Population: 61.0m GDP per head: $36,100 (PPP: $32,700)</p>

<p>Silvio Berlusconi, assailed at home by the courts and the victims of austerity and abroad by the financial markets, will not make it to the 2013 elections; a national-unity government will probably be convened to serve out his term. Euro woes have focused attention on Italy's dysfunctional economy, and policy will move in response to the market's concern about the country's ability to grow its way out of danger. Fiscal tightening will narrow the budget gap but also weigh down the economy, which will contract in 2012.Â </p>

